SIMPLE: tres-tyne
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Tres-tyne
<hw>Tres"-tyne`</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>tris</ets>, <ets>tres</ets>, three + E. <ets>tyne</ets>.]</ety>
<fld>(Zool.)</fld> <def>In the antler of a stag, the third tyne above
the base. This tyne appears in the third year. In those deer in which
the brow tyne does not divide, the tres-tyne is the second tyne above
the base. See <xex>Illust.</xex> under <er>Rucervine</er>, and under
<er>Rusine</er>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Tret</ent>⟦br⟧
